    {
      "id": "PopularPost161636",
      "post_content": "Playing a disruption spell ([Terror](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Terror), [Duress](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Duress), [Counterspell](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counterspell), ect.) can save you eight life for the same amount of mana. Playing a disruption spell could also help you force your own creatures through, and thus help you win the game. Playing a disruption spell would help deal with creatures that have a non-damage-related ability ([Leonin Arbiter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leonin Arbiter), as one example), whereas Rest for the Weary won't.\n  \n   \nWhy not play a card that interacts with the opponet, rather than passively padding your life total? Barring interactions with cards such as [False Cure](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=False Cure) or [Test of Endurance](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Test of Endurance), there is no advantage to playing a disruption spell over a card that only gains more life, as the former cards are much more versatile and reliable. ",
      "posted_by": "scumbling1",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost161636\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Playing a disruption spell (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Terror\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Terror\">Terror</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Duress\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Duress\">Duress</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Counterspell\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counterspell\">Counterspell</a>, ect.)  can save you eight life for the same amount of mana. Playing a disruption spell could also help you force your own creatures through, and thus help you win the game. Playing a disruption spell would help deal with creatures that have a non-damage-related ability (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Leonin Arbiter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leonin Arbiter\">Leonin Arbiter</a>, as one example), whereas Rest for the Weary won't.\r<br/> <br/>Why not play a card that interacts with the opponet, rather than passively padding your life total? Barring interactions with cards such as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"False Cure\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=False Cure\">False Cure</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Test of Endurance\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Test of Endurance\">Test of Endurance</a>, there is no advantage to playing a disruption spell over a card that only gains more life, as the former cards are much more versatile and reliable. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '161636'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy3892\">scumbling1</span>\r\n                                (5/17/2011 6:06:04 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
